EFFURUN – The Petroleum Training Institute, Effurun Warri Delta State today Friday, 18th February, 2022 organized a combined Matriculation Ceremony for a total number of one thousand two hundred and sixty seven students (1267) for the 20021/2022 Academic Session for both full time and School of lndustrial Continuing Education Programme. The well attended event which took place at the Conference Centre of the Petroleum Training lnstitute on the NPA/DSC Express Way Was declared opened by Dr Henry Adimula the Principle/ Chief Executive Officer of the lnstitute flanked by Members of the Academic Board of the lnstitute. Dr Henry Adimula, the Principal/Chief Executive Officer of PTI Effurun in his official address thanked all Members of the Academic Board , Deans of Study,Heads of Department, allManagement and Staff of the Petroleum Training Institute for the successful 2021/2022 Academic Session Matriculation Ceremony being organized for Fulltime and School of lndustrial Continuing Education in the Great and Unique Petroleum Training lnstitute Which is the first of it’s kind in Africa. Borno Students’ Union Bounces Back Bauchi Students Commend Governor Mohammed For Payment Of 5033… Dr Henry Adimula the PTI Chief Executive stated in his speech that PTl was established by Act NO 37 of 1972 and subsequently amended by Act No 52 of 1975 by FA CAP P16 , Laws of the Federation of Nigeria, 2004 which mandated the lnstitute to provide courses of instruction , training and research in technology and in the development of Technologists and Technicians required for the Oil, gas and allied industries . The PTI boss pointed out saying: ” The Institute’s Vision and Missions statement has been the guiding principles within which we operate as an lnstitute and I want you to know and imbibe them as you sojourn with us in good fate. Speaking further, he added: “The vision of PTl is to become the leading oil and gas technological lnstitute in Africa and maintain the tempo through continuous update of new frontiers of knowledge while our mission is to Provide competent technological human resources through quality training, research and consultancy for the Petroleum and allied industry.” Dr Henry Adimula who informed the audience of some remarkable academic milestones achieved by the lnstitute said: “The National Skill Qualification Framework ( NSQF) has been introduced into the PTI educational system , essentially to develop, to classify and recognize skills knowledge and competence that is required by individuals irrespective of how the skills and training were acquired.” He disclosed that the programme is a highbred certification System which have allowance for continuous training of competent hands for the Oil and gas industry, ensuring collaborative synergy between PTI and the oil and gas industry, noting that some of the staff of PTl has been certified as Assessors of the NSQF Programme. POLL While addressing the Matriculants specifically he said: “Let me at this juncture congratulate all the Matriculants who have been found suitable for admission into this unique citadel of leaning. Today’s event marks an important milestone in your lives as Matriculants, as it signifies your official admission into the Petroleum Training Institute after the completion of the registration formalities and the taking of the Matriculation oath at the end of this ceremony .” Dr Adimula the Academic Don who stressed the need for the students to avoid all sorts of behaviour capable of truncating their studentship disclosed that the Matriculating students after passing the Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination and the Post Jamb for the National Diploma and the HND Interviews for the HND candidates, the Matriculating students are amongst the successful Lucky ones as a total of 1,480 candidates applied for admission into the National Diploma programmes , but only 720 candidates were offered admission while for the Higher National Diploma programmes, 714 candidates applied , but only 547 candidates were offered admission. In his summation Adimula said; “Distinguished ladies and gentlemen, PTI has come of age , this year we shall celebrate our golden jubilee , In the last fifty ( 50 ) years we have trained over twenty thousand (20,000 ) students who are now in every facet of the oil , gas and allied industries in Nigeria and all over the world”, he concluded.